The paper deals with information transmission and decoding in a discrete time channel with additive Gaussian noise, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of feedback channel and investigation of achievable decoding error exponent also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The mention of transmission of nonexponential number of messages and the use of a specific method for transmission/decoding also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG).
